chunk_content: 184 Specimen received for testing: A specimen is received for testing if its arrival at the laboratory-based testing site was recorded in a register/logbook and/or LIS within the reporting timeframe. A specimen received for testing may or may not have been tested/analyzed. H E A DEFINITIONS (POINT-OF-CARE TESTING SITES): L T POCT site: H A. The site performs testing near or at the place of interaction with the patient/client. S B. The site performs testing in an environment which does not have a formal laboratory Y infrastructure. S C. Testing at the POCT site is performed by healthcare workers who may not be laboratorians. T E D. Conducting POCT in one or more of the following areas: M a. HIV rapid test S b. Infant Virologic Testing / Early Infant Diagnosis (IVT/EID) c. HIV viral load d. TB diagnostics: molecular WHO-recommended diagnostic (mWRD), LF-LAM, or AFB e. CD4 testing f.
